<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He proudly flaunted his bizarre half-shaved mullet on Thursday evening. </p>

<p>And shortly after debuting his new look, former AFL star Brendan Fevola took to the streets of Melbourne to show off his questionable new 'do.</p>

<p>The 39-year-old was seen out for a stroll amid the city'shard lockdown, dressed down in a white T-shirt and blue shorts.</p>

<p>He woke up like this! Former AFL star Brendan Fevola flaunted his BIZARRE half-shaved mullet haircut while out for a stroll during Melbourne's hard lockdown on Friday </p>

<p>He also had on his face mask that has 'not today rona' emblazoned across the front.</p>

<p>As he looked down at his car keys, the FOX FM radio host's odd hairstyle was on full display, with Brendan revealing the bare top and sides and the dark curly locks on the back of his head.  </p>

<p>On Thursday, Brendan shared a photo on Instagram showing the bald front of his head and the remaining part of his mane. </p>

<p>That's different!  As he looked down at his car keys, the FOX FM radio host's odd hairstyle was on full display, with Brendan revealing the bare top and sides and the dark curly locks on the back of his head</p>

<p>He hilariously captioned the snap: 'Looking grouse 2020'.</p>

<p>It comes after Brendan unveiled several dramatic looks back in Melbourne's April lockdown. </p>

<p>The sports star dyed his hair green and purple to represent his employer's trademark logo.</p>

<p>'Looking grouse 2020':  On Thursday, Brendan shared a photo on Instagram showing the bald front of his head and the remaining part of his mane</p>

